y in the world with its headquarters in toronto ontario canada barrick is currently undertaking mining projects in argentina australia canada chile the dominican republic papua new guinea peru saudi arabia the united states and zambia for  it produced  million ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of us ounce and  million pounds of copper at c cash costs of pound as of december   its proven and probable mineral reserves were  million ounces  us tons of gold  million ounces of silver contained within gold reserves and  billion pounds of copper on january   barrick acquired a majority share of placer dome the production of the combined organization moved barrick to its current position as the largest gold producer ahead of newmont mining corporation in  barrick produced  million ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce copper production for the year totaled  million pounds at allin sustaining cash costs of  per pound  in q  barrick generated us billion in revenue and produced  million ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce  contents  history  founding and early years   to   placer dome acquisition   to present  operations  argentina  australia  canada  chile  dominican republic  papua new guinea  peru  saudi arabia  united states  zambia  mining practices  relations to local populations  renewable energy  legal controversy  environmental issues  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit founding and early yearsedit barrick gold corporation evolved from a privately held north american oil and gas company barrick resources after suffering huge financial losses in oil and gas principal peter munk decided to focus on gold barrick resources corporation became a publicly traded company on may   listing on the toronto stock exchange the company’s first acquisition was the renabie mine near wawa ontario which produced around  troy ounces  t of gold in  but its best year was  with  ounces produced in  barrick acquired camflo mining which had operations in the province of quebec and in the us state of nevada barrick’s effort to purchase was slowed by skepticism the company could assume camflo’s debt of around  million the sale was finalized in may  with terms that obligated barrick to repay the debt to the royal bank of canada within one year the debt was fully paid in january  barrick resource’s next acquisition was the mercur mine in mercur utah in june  followed by the goldstrike mine in nevada in  the goldstrike mine is located on the carlin trend  to edit the company’s name was changed to american barrick resources in  it was listed on the new york stock exchange in february  the name was changed to the present barrick gold corporation in  in a  friendly takeover american barrick became the third largest gold mining company in the world when it acquired the canadian mining company lac minerals which owned properties in north and south america two years later in  arequipa resources owner of properties including the pierina mine in peru accepted a takeover offer from the renamed barrick gold corporation worth about usd  a third acquisition followed in early  when barrick gold acquired sutton resources ltd for around  million in stock assuming ownership of properties in tanzania in  barrick gold made another stock deal worth about usd  billion to buy the homestake mining company then one of the oldest mining companies in the united states the purchase moved barrick to second largest gold producer in the world placer dome acquisitionedit the company offered us  billion for placer dome inc in a bid announced october   during the following weeks placer dome recommended shareholders reject the offer in december placer dome’s board of directors approved an increased offer worth us  billion the transaction closed in early  making barrick the world’s largest gold producer  to presentedit on july   barrick announced their intent to purchase novagold resources and pioneer metals the unsolicited bid for novagold resources was at us  billion or us  per share and the solicited bid for pioneer metals was at us  million or us  per share novagold management quickly characterized barricks bid for their company as undervalued pioneer management however quickly endorsed barricks bid for their company previously on june   novagold made an unsolicited bid for pioneer metals at us  million novagold and pioneer are currently in litigation over the grace project in british columbia canada that project is adjacent to novagolds galore creek project and  kilometers away from barricks eskay creek mine novagold and barrick also cross paths at the donlin creek project in alaska where novagold is  owner and barrick is  owner however barrick has the right to earn in a  share as a result of their takeover of placer dome in january  on august   novagold filed a lawsuit in british columbia canada alleging that barrick misused confidential information to make its bid for pioneer metals as part of the suit novagold is asking that any shares tendered to barrick under the pioneer bid be held in a trust for novagold on august   novagold filed a second lawsuit against barrick – this time in the district of alaska court alleging that barrick violated us security laws by misrepresenting its position by repeatedly stating it is ontrack to earn a  interest in the donlin creek mine the suit sought a temporary suspension of barricks hostile bid for novagold on december   after extending the bid for novagold  times increasing the offer once and lowering the threshold for takeup of tendered shares from  to  and then to no minimum barrick finally let the bid expire the net result for barrick was a takeup of  of the outstanding novagold shares barricks then chief executive greg wilkins indicated that the company would look elsewhere for acquisition opportunities more recently the company was reported to be eyeing aurelian resources in ecuador in november  novagold and teck cominco announced the suspension of galore creek project and nova gold share plummeted during the summer and autumn of  nova gold tried to put their rock creek project in alaska into production after less than two months of operation production was shut down for obscure reasons on january   nova gold announced a  million dollar private placement for a  control in the company valuing the company at approximately  million dollars or  of the price offered by barrick two years earlier through  and  the company offered a usd  million prize to the scientific community in a bid to improve silver recovery rates at its veladero mine in argentina recovery rates for silver were below  because the metal is bound within silica which is difficult to dissolve using conventional cyanidation processing  researchers from  countries registered as participants with  proposals submitted nine proposals were selected for testing barrick gold created the largest stock offering in canadian history during  when it issued a  billion equity offering which was increased the following day to  billion in response to market demand revenue from the offering was used to eliminate the company’s gold hedges which locked in the sale price of future production rather than selling it at market prices in february  barrick gold announced plans to create a separate company to hold its assets in tanzania called african barrick gold barrick gold would retain majority ownership in the new company after its listing on the london stock exchange african barrick gold was listed on the london stock exchange in midmarch  with an ipo valuation at us billion the shares offered on the lse raised just more than  million pounds in june the company was admitted to the ftse  index in april  barrick beat a takeover offer for equinox minerals by china minmetals in august  barrick agreed to sell its yilgarn south assets in western australia to south africa’s gold fields for us million divesting its granny smith darlot and lawlers mine operations in july  barrick announced changes to its executive management structure kevin dushnisky and jim gowans current coo have been appointed as copresidents taking responsibility for execution of the companys operating plans and strategic priorities current cfo ammar aljoundi is being promoted to senior executive vice president in conjunction with the restructuring jamie sokalsky will be stepping down effective september   in march  barrick and antofagasta plc announced that an arbitration tribunal of the world banks international center for settlement of investment disputes had issued a decision in favor of the parties and that the islamic republic of pakistan had unlawfully denied a mining lease for the reko diq mine project in  reko diq is located in the balochistan province of pakistan and was expected to require an initial capital investment of more than us billion and is one of the worlds largest undeveloped copper and gold deposits  in  barrick reported it had formed a  joint venture with goldcorp to consolidate the cerro casale project in chile as well as acquire exeter resource corporation  operationsedit barrick is organized into ten operating units • five individual gold mines – cortez goldstrike pueblo viejo lagunas norte and veladero • two gold mine portfolios – north america other and australia pacific •  equity interest in african barrick gold plc • one global copper business • one project pascualama argentinaedit veladero mine in april  barrick announced it had sold a  interest in the veladero mine to shandong gold for us million  australiaedit cowal gold mine super pit gold mine  ownership canadaedit hemlo gold mine chileedit pascua lama zaldivar copper mine  ownership in april  barrick announced it had formed a partnership with shandong gold to explore jointdevelopment of the pascualama deposit  dominican republicedit pueblo viejo mine  ownership papua new guineaedit porgera gold mine  ownership peruedit lagunas norte mine pierina gold mine saudi ar